{"title":"Spotlight: Warmfront Chest Warmer","link":"https://cyclingtips.com/2021/03/spotlight-warmfront-chest-warmer/","date":1616455500000,"content":"<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-3 is-cropped wp-block-gallery__slider\"><ul class=\"blocks-gallery-grid\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"754\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-1-1340x754.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"504563\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-1.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/the-warmfront-adds-a-little-extra-warmth-right-on-the-front-of-your-torso/\" class=\"wp-image-504563\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-1-1340x754.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-1-650x366.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-1-190x107.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-1-1080x608.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-1-16x9.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-1.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">The Warmfront adds a little extra warmth right on the front of your torso.</figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"754\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-5-1340x754.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"504572\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-5.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/the-idea-might-silly-but-it-works-as-advertised/\" class=\"wp-image-504572\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-5-1340x754.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-5-650x366.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-5-190x107.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-5-1080x608.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-5-16x9.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-5.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">The idea might seem silly, but it works as advertised.</figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"754\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-2-1340x754.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"504564\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-2.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/warmfront-2/\" class=\"wp-image-504564\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-2-1340x754.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-2-650x366.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-2-190x107.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-2-1080x608.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-2-16x9.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-2.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">Three different levels of warmth and protection are available, including a lightweight waffle-pattern fleece (right), the same fabric with a layer of windproof material (center), and a heavier-weight fleece with a windproof layer laminated in the middle (left).</figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"754\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-3-1340x754.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"504566\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-3.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/warmfront-3/\" class=\"wp-image-504566\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-3-1340x754.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-3-650x366.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-3-190x107.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-3-1080x608.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-3-16x9.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-3.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">The waffle-pattern fleece doesn&#8217;t look like much, but it&#8217;s impressively warm considering how much it compresses.</figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"754\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-4-1340x754.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"504569\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-4.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/warmfront-4/\" class=\"wp-image-504569\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-4-1340x754.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-4-650x366.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-4-190x107.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-4-1080x608.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-4-16x9.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Warmfront-4.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">Two of the Warmfront models feature Velcro collars so they&#8217;re easy to get on and off as needed. The heavy-duty model incorporates a fleece neck gaiter.</figcaption></figure></li></ul></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>We already have a wealth of good options for helping us stay warm and cozy during the cooler mornings and evenings as the world makes the transition between winter and summer. Vests/gilets? Ultralight jackets? Windproof jerseys? Check, check, and check.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So do we really need another one? Maybe.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Warmfront is an upstart Colorado company offering a modern (and far more functional) take on the old-fashioned dickey. Just as the name suggests, these chest warmers add an extra layer right on the front of your torso, where it’s arguably needed most.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>There are three versions available. The Ultralight uses a waffle-pattern fleece body, whereas the Koselig (&#8220;cozy&#8221; in Norwegian) incorporates an additional windproof layer for extra protection. Both include high-cut collars with Velcro closures for easy on-and-off and several pattern choices for the collar. Finally, there’s the Warmfront Max, which uses a more traditional fleece material for insulation, but with a laminated windproof layer and built-in waffle-pattern fleece neck warmer. All of them roll up super small (smaller than a pair of arm warmers) to easily tuck away in a jersey pocket.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Warmfront even offers custom sizing — possible only because of the small-batch, local manufacturing — and the company also has a &#8220;<a href=\"https://www.thewarmfront.com/buy-one-give-one.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Buy One Give One</a>&#8221; program whereby a special Warmfront is donated to a breast cancer survivor for every one purchased at retail.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Do these look a little silly? Well, by themselves, sure — but they’re not supposed to be visible, anyway. And wouldn’t a vest do the same thing while keeping the windproof layer on the very outside? Yes again, but they also don’t feel quite as warm, either.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Silliness aside, I have to admit after using these for a few weeks that they actually work pretty well, and they’ve also been handy for other activities like skiing. And truth be told, I haven’t found them to be a replacement for a vest or jacket, but rather a good addition to one to expand the comfortable temperature range of my kit even further. The pricing isn’t too bad, either.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Price: </strong>US$29-39 / AU$40-50</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>More information: </strong><a href=\"http://www.thewarmfront.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">www.thewarmfront.com</a></p>\n\n\n<p>    <div data-block-name=\"highlight-box\" class=\"highlight-box \" id=\"\">\n    <div class=\"highlight-box__inner-container\">\n\t<em>Follow the link to see previous products we&#8217;ve reviewed in our <a href=\"https://cyclingtips.com/tag/spotlight/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Spotlight series</a>.</em>    </div>\n    </div>\n\t</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://cyclingtips.com/2021/03/spotlight-warmfront-chest-warmer/\">Spotlight: Warmfront Chest Warmer</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://cyclingtips.com\">CyclingTips</a>.</p>","author":"James Huang","siteTitle":"CyclingTips","siteHash":"30feca30fb3902119bf2da6559e7337232527b61c9abe0a00f5d7543c6aa6c84","entryHash":"1367ed2a961bb83d464cf1dde91c415fe9ec16575e75c99246551f6208ab0120","category":"Cycling"}